<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: beercules</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-03 09:03:20</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Just got this bow last night, and I wanted to share my info with everyone else. To get the quest, go to felwith and talk to Kinool Oresinger I think his name his (hes in the enchaners guild). Ask him, what is the Rain Caller? and he will give the quest to you. Components needed are:<BR>
<BR>
Trueshot Longbow (about 150pp from a player)<BR>
Wooden Heart (off a Treant, or from Jyle Windshot in WFP)<BR>
GOLD Fairy Dust (from Princess Jenoola or something like   that. Shes in Lfay in the Faerie town thingie. AND NO, She does not always spawn by Gearheart, I spent 8 hours waiting for her, and she didnt spawn there. Have a higher up char or something kill the faeries, cause good luck getting the bow if she wont talk to you.<BR>
<BR>
Also Required is 3000gp as a nominal fee for enchanting the bow. All this is given at the same time to kinool.<BR>
<BR>
As for getting the dust, this is the hardest part of the quest. You will need to get the princess'es wing from Sanfryd Featherhead in Ak'Anon. Tell him you are his friend, then once he gives you his box, fill it with 10 ( non stacked) Fuzzlecutter Formula 5000's from Ping Fuzzlecutter in West Freeport. Once that is done, he will give you a tattered toupee which you will need repaired by ping. <BR>
<BR>
      In order to get it repaired, you need 2 clumps of gorilla hair (off Hulking gorillas in Cazic-thule) and a lock of haif off the Golden Haired mermaid in Kedge Keep. Once you have all 4 items, give them to Ping and he will give you the Mane Attraction, which you then give to sanfryd. He will give you the wing for helping him, which you then give to the princess when she actually spawns, and she will give you the dust. And, once again, have someone kill the Faeries for you until she spawns. Once you have the dust, just turn in your Trueshot, dust, wood heart and the 3000gp and you have a raincaller!<BR>
</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
