<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Calador</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-06-28 11:33:48</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Ok, just my experience on this quest, I am currently only lvl 32 but I should finish the quest tonight and get my raincaller if I can catch princess joleena.  I got the gorilla hair for the quest when I was about lvl 23, I spent quite a bit of time in Cazic in my mid 20s, and the gorilla hair is very easy to get, just ask whoever is camping the Tae ew Templar room for them, they will probably let you have them in a heart beat.  The mermaid hair was a little harder, but not much really.  The name of the mermaid that drops it is litteraly "a golden haired mermaid", the room just beneath hers is very easy to camp and pull solo to, so many people camp it for experience.  I just swam in one night, asked if anyone was camping her, then when someone said yes, I asked if I could loot the hair, they said yes, I swam in and got it, and got out.  It is very easy to get to the spot to loot the hair without being attacke, you just need to know exactly where to go, and don't stop.  Just my experience though, good luck rangers.</font></td></tr></table>
